step_data.thought:
I received a TimeoutError when trying to click on the radio button with BID '328'. The error message indicates that the label element (BID '329') is intercepting the pointer events, which is preventing the click on the radio button itself. This is a common scenario with styled radio buttons where the label is used to capture clicks.

Instead of clicking on the radio button directly, I should click on its label which has BID '329'. This will effectively select the 'Just me' option.

Before I do that, I also need to fill in the required fields for the group creation:
1. I need to fill in the 'Group name' field (BID '257')
2. The 'Group URL' will be auto-generated but might need adjustment (BID '267')

Let me first fill in the Group name field, then I'll click on the 'Just me' label.
